body.description: For above average power and longer battery life, the ADX12-BS is the perfect choice. This AGM (Absorbed Glass Mat) battery is maintenance free, sealed and non spillable. It never needs refilling and meets, or exceeds, the power demands of your ride. The spill proof heat selaed cover means no leaks and the sulfation resistant plates provide longer battery life. Because the ADX12-BS is a premium sealed battery it holds voltage longer which means this battery is ready when you are. The ADX12-BS meets, or exceeds, the specifications of your rides original battery. Using the highest quality materials and workmanship available allow the ADX12-BS to enjoy an extended life and extremely low discharge rate. This factory fresh battery is guaranteed to fit your ride and perform beyond your expectations. It is shipped fully charged and ready to install out of the box. With ThrottleX just buy and ride. With Confidence.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 28, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solid Battery…so far…
reviews.reviewText: This battery was replacing a 4-year old Yuasa that was amazing. I thought I’d test it out and it seems to be doing well. I keep the bike on a trickle charger when not riding to help longevity.Cranking, it seems weak but always fires up. I have not had any issues with it yet here in Florida.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 4, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Battery - Highly Recommend.
reviews.reviewText: Battery came extremely well packaged and protected from damage. I removed the old battery in my 2008 Suzuki Boulevard M50 and this battery was a direct fit with absolutely no trouble to install. I turned the key, and the bike fired right up. This battery was much cheaper than a lot of other options out there, but the cheaper only applies to the price, not the quality or performance. I am not a weekly rider, so my bike sits for weeks at a time without being touched, but I like knowing that with this battery, when I do go to start it, it will start.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2016
reviews.reviewText: This battery fits my Kawasaki vulcan 900 custom. It was well packaged and a fast delivery time. When i opened the box i put the battery straight on the bike and it started right away and has done ever since. I have had this for a year now and not done a thing to it. The price was very good compared to store prices. I think i paid around $70 for my last one in SAM'S and didn't last 6 months. I am only a weekend warrior so the bike has a battery tender connected everyday. I will buy another again hopefully not too soon.
